OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1781348571
OL,3,CWelsh people awarded the King's
OL,4,Cbirthday honours
OL,6,FDr Inderpal Singh, the national
OL,7,Fclinical lead for falls and frailty,
OL,8,Freceived an award for his
OL,9,Ftransformative services to
OL,10,Fosteoporosis care in Wales.
OL,12,FMeanwhile, Helen Whyley, executive
OL,13,Fdirector of the Royal College of
OL,14,FNursing (RCN) Wales, was honoured for
OL,15,Fher services to the nursing
OL,16,Fprofession, and Professor Margaret
OL,17,FJoan Allan, lately the pharmacy dean
OL,18,Fat Health Education and Improvement
OL,19,FWales, was recognised for her services
OL,20,Fto pharmacy.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/8
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
