SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1781348571
OL,3,CWelsh people awarded the King's
OL,4,Cbirthday honours
OL,6,FStephen John Hughson: From Newbridge
OL,7,Fon Wye, Powys, recognised for his
OL,8,Fexceptional services to Agriculture,
OL,9,FTourism, and major events, helping to
OL,10,Fkeep rural Welsh industries thriving.
OL,12,FAnd on this year's list is footballing
OL,13,Ficon Cliff Jones, who has been made an
OL,14,FMBE for his services to Welsh football.
OL,16,FJones was an integral part of
OL,17,FTottenham Hotspur's famous 1961 double-
OL,18,Fwinning side and played for Wales
OL,19,Fduring their historic 1958 World Cup
OL,20,Fcampaign in Sweden.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/8
